080/**
081 *  The abstract base class for the implementations of
082 *  {@link TypeSpec}.
083 *
084 *  @author Square,Inc.
085 *  @modified   Thomas Thrien - thomas.thrien@tquadrat.org
086 *  @version $Id: TypeSpecImpl.java 1085 2024-01-05 16:23:28Z tquadrat $
087 *  @since 0.0.5
088 *
089 *  @UMLGraph.link
090 */
091@SuppressWarnings( {"ClassWithTooManyFields", "OverlyCoupledClass"} )
092@ClassVersion( sourceVersion = "$Id: TypeSpecImpl.java 1085 2024-01-05 16:23:28Z tquadrat $" )
093@API( status = INTERNAL, since = "0.0.5" )
094public abstract sealed class TypeSpecImpl implements TypeSpec
095    permits AnnotationTypeSpecImpl, ClassSpecImpl, EnumSpecImpl, InterfaceSpecImpl, RecordSpecImpl
096{
097        /*---------------*\
098    ====** Inner Classes **====================================================
099        \*---------------*/
100    /**
101     *  The abstract base class for the implementations of
102     *  {@link org.tquadrat.foundation.javacomposer.TypeSpec.Builder}.
103     *
104     *  @author Square,Inc.
105     *  @modified Thomas Thrien - thomas.thrien@tquadrat.org
106     *  @version $Id: TypeSpecImpl.java 1085 2024-01-05 16:23:28Z tquadrat $
107     *  @since 0.0.5
108     *
109     *  @UMLGraph.link
110     */
111    @SuppressWarnings( "OverlyCoupledClass" )
112    @ClassVersion( sourceVersion = "$Id: TypeSpecImpl.java 1085 2024-01-05 16:23:28Z tquadrat $" )
113    @API( status = INTERNAL, since = "0.0.5" )
114    public abstract static sealed class BuilderImpl implements TypeSpec.Builder
115        permits AnnotationTypeSpecImpl.BuilderImpl, ClassSpecImpl.BuilderImpl, EnumSpecImpl.BuilderImpl, InterfaceSpecImpl.BuilderImpl, RecordSpecImpl.BuilderImpl
116    {

216        /**
217         *  Creates a new {@code BuilderImpl} instance.
218         *
219         *  @param  composer    The reference to the factory that created this
220         *      builder instance.
221         *  @param  kind    The kind of the type to build.
222         *  @param  name    The name of the type to build.
223         */
224        protected BuilderImpl( @SuppressWarnings( "UseOfConcreteClass" ) final JavaComposer composer, final Kind kind, final CharSequence name )
225        {
226            this( composer, kind, Optional.of( requireNotEmptyArgument( name, "name" ).toString() ) );
227        }   //  BuilderImpl()
228
229        /**
230         *  Creates a new {@code BuilderImpl} instance for an anonymous type.
231         *
232         *  @param  composer    The reference to the factory that created this
233         *      builder instance.
234         *  @param  kind    The kind of the type to build.
235         */
236        protected BuilderImpl( @SuppressWarnings( "UseOfConcreteClass" ) final JavaComposer composer, final Kind kind )
237        {
238            this( composer, kind, Optional.empty() );
239        }   //  BuilderImpl()
240
241        /**
242         *  Creates a new {@code BuilderImpl} instance.
243         *
244         *  @param  composer    The reference to the factory that created this
245         *      builder instance.
246         *  @param  kind    The kind of the type to build.
247         *  @param  name    The name of the type to build.
248         */
249        @SuppressWarnings( {"OptionalUsedAsFieldOrParameterType", "OptionalGetWithoutIsPresent"} )
250        protected BuilderImpl( @SuppressWarnings( "UseOfConcreteClass" ) final JavaComposer composer, final Kind kind, final Optional<String> name )
251        {
252            m_Composer = requireNonNullArgument( composer, "composer" );
253            m_Kind = requireNonNullArgument( kind, "kind" );
254            m_Name = requireValidNonNullArgument( name, "name", v -> v.isEmpty() || isValidName( v.get() ), _ -> "not a valid name: %s".formatted( name.get() ) );
255
256            m_InitializerBlock = (CodeBlockImpl.BuilderImpl) m_Composer.codeBlockBuilder();
257            m_Javadoc = (CodeBlockImpl.BuilderImpl) m_Composer.codeBlockBuilder();
258            m_StaticBlock = (CodeBlockImpl.BuilderImpl) m_Composer.codeBlockBuilder();
259        }   //  BuilderImpl()
260

346        {

348                .addJavadoc( format, args )

350            addEnumConstant( name, anonymousClass );
351
352            //---* Done *------------------------------------------------------
353            return this;
354        }   //  addEnumConstant()

359        @Override

361        {
362            throw new IllegalStateException( "%s is not enum".formatted( m_Name.orElse( NAME_ANONYMOUS_TYPE ) ) );
363        }   //  addEnumConstant()

365        /**
366         *  {@inheritDoc}
367         */
368        @Override
369        public BuilderImpl addField( final FieldSpec fieldSpec )
370        {
371            final var fieldSpecImpl = (FieldSpecImpl) requireNonNullArgument( fieldSpec, "fieldSpec" );
372            if( composer().addDebugOutput() )
373            {
374                final var builder = fieldSpecImpl.toBuilder();
375                createDebugOutput( true ).ifPresent( debug -> builder.addJavadoc( "\n$L\n", debug.asLiteral() ) );
376                m_FieldSpecs.add( builder.build() );
377            }
378            else
379            {
380                m_FieldSpecs.add( fieldSpecImpl );
381            }
382
383            final var maxFields = composer().getMaxFields();
384            if( (maxFields > 0) && (m_FieldSpecs.size() >= maxFields) )
385            {
386                addSuppressableWarning( CLASS_WITH_TOO_MANY_FIELDS );
387            }
388
389            //---* Done *------------------------------------------------------
390            return this;
391        }   //  addField()
392
393        /**
394         *  {@inheritDoc}
395         */
396        @Override
397        public final BuilderImpl addField( final Type type, final CharSequence name, final Modifier... modifiers )
398        {
399            return addField( TypeNameImpl.from( type ), name, modifiers );
400        }   //  addField()

447                .ifPresent( debug -> m_Javadoc.addWithoutDebugInfo( debug.asLiteral() ) );

490        /**
491         *  {@inheritDoc}
492         */
493        @Override
494        public final BuilderImpl addModifiers( final Modifier... modifiers )
495        {
496            checkState( !isAnonymousClass(), () -> new IllegalStateException( "forbidden on anonymous types." ) );
497            for( final var modifier : requireNonNullArgument( modifiers, "modifiers" ) )
498            {
499                checkState( nonNull( modifier ), () -> new ValidationException( "modifiers contain null" ) );
500                m_Modifiers.add( modifier );
501            }
502
503            //---* Done *------------------------------------------------------
504            return this;
505        }   //  addModifiers()

549        /**
550         *  {@inheritDoc}
551         */
552        @API( status = STABLE, since = "0.2.0" )
553        @Override
554        public final BuilderImpl addStaticImport( final ClassName className, final String... names )
555        {
556            final var canonicalName = requireNonNullArgument( className, "className" ).canonicalName();
557            for( final var name : requireValidNonNullArgument( names, "names", v -> v.length > 0, "%s array is empty"::formatted ) )
558            {
559                m_StaticImports.add(
560                    format(
561                        "%s.%s",
562                        canonicalName,
563                        requireValidArgument(
564                            name,
565                            "name",
566                            Objects::nonNull,
567                            _ -> "null entry in names array: %s".formatted( Arrays.toString( names ) )
568                        )
569                    )
570                );
571            }
572
573            //---* Done *------------------------------------------------------
574            return this;
575        }   //  addStaticImport()
576

663        /**
664         *  {@inheritDoc}
665         */
666        @Override
667        public final BuilderImpl addType( final TypeSpec typeSpec )
668        {
669            final var typeSpecImpl = (TypeSpecImpl) requireNonNullArgument( typeSpec, "typeSpec" );
670            checkState( typeSpecImpl.modifiers().containsAll( m_Kind.implicitTypeModifiers() ), () -> new ValidationException( "%s %s.%s requires modifiers %s".formatted( m_Kind, m_Name.orElse( NAME_ANONYMOUS_TYPE ), typeSpecImpl.name().orElse( NAME_ANONYMOUS_TYPE ), m_Kind.implicitTypeModifiers() ) ) );
671            if( composer().addDebugOutput() )
672            {
673                final var builder = typeSpecImpl.toBuilder();
674                createDebugOutput( true ).ifPresent( debug -> builder.addJavadoc( "\n$L\n", debug.asLiteral() ) );
675                m_TypeSpecs.add( builder.build() );
676            }
677            else
678            {
679                m_TypeSpecs.add( typeSpecImpl );
680            }
681
682            //---* Done *------------------------------------------------------
683            return this;
684        }   //  addType()

693            {
694                addType( typeSpec );
695            }
696
697            //---* Done *------------------------------------------------------
698            return this;
699        }   //  addTypes()

707            checkState( !isAnonymousClass(), () -> new IllegalStateException( "forbidden on anonymous types." ) );
708            m_TypeVariables.add( (TypeVariableNameImpl) requireNonNullArgument( typeVariable, "typeVariable" ) );
709
710            //---* Done *------------------------------------------------------
711            return this;
712        }   //  addTypeVariable()

714        /**
715         *  {@inheritDoc}
716         */
717        @API( status = STABLE, since = "0.2.0" )
718        @Override
719        public final BuilderImpl addTypeVariable( final TypeVariableName typeVariable, final CharSequence javadoc )
720        {
721            final var retValue = addTypeVariable( typeVariable );
722            createDebugOutput( m_Composer.addDebugOutput() )
723                .ifPresent( v -> m_Javadoc.addWithoutDebugInfo( v.asLiteral() ) );
724            m_Javadoc.addWithoutDebugInfo(
725                """
726                \n@param <$L> $S
727                """, typeVariable, requireNotEmptyArgument( javadoc, "javadoc" ) );
728
729            //---* Done *------------------------------------------------------
730            return retValue;
731        }   //  addTypeVariable()

734         *  {@inheritDoc}
735         */

737        public final BuilderImpl addTypeVariables( final Iterable<TypeVariableName> typeVariables )
738        {
739            requireNonNullArgument( typeVariables, "typeVariables" );
740            checkState( !isAnonymousClass(), () -> new IllegalStateException( "forbidden on anonymous types." ) );
741            for( final var typeVariable : typeVariables )
742            {
743                m_TypeVariables.add( (TypeVariableNameImpl) typeVariable );
744            }
745
746            //---* Done *------------------------------------------------------
747            return this;
748        }   //  addTypeVariables()

1261    /**
1262     *  Compares two instances of
1263     *  {@link MethodSpec}
1264     *  for their sort order.
1265     *
1266     *  @param  m1  The first method spec.
1267     *  @param  m2  The second method spec.
1268     *  @return -1 if the first method spec will be sorted before the second,
1269     *      1 if the first method spec will be sorted after the second, and
1270     *      0 if both are equals.
1271     */
1272    protected static final int compareMethodSpecs( final MethodSpec m1, final MethodSpec m2 )
1273    {
1274        var retValue = Integer.signum( m1.name().compareToIgnoreCase( m2.name() ) );
1275        if( retValue == 0 )
1276        {
1277            /*
1278             * MethodSpec.toString() returns the whole method, including the
1279             * modifiers and the return value. But for the sorting, we only
1280             * want to have the signature – that is the name plus the arguments
1281             * list.
1282             * We know already that the name is equal, and we know also that
1283             * the arguments list must be different (okay, we do NOT know that
1284             * for sure, but it does not make sense if not). So we can strip
1285             * everything before the name and compare the remainder.
1286             */
1287            final var name = m1.name();
1288            var s1 = m1.toString();
1289            var pos = s1.indexOf( name );
1290            s1 = s1.substring( pos );
1291
1292            var s2 = m2.toString();
1293            pos = s2.indexOf( name );
1294            s2 = s2.substring( pos );
1295
1296            retValue = Integer.signum( s1.compareToIgnoreCase( s2 ) );
1297        }
1298
1299        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
1300        return retValue;
1301    }   //  compareMethodSpecs()

1312    /**
1313     *  Emit the type to the given code writer.
1314     *
1315     *  @param  codeWriter  The target code writer.
1316     *  @param  enumName    The name of the enum; will be {@code null} if not
1317     *      called to emit an enum constant.
1318     *  @param  implicitModifiers   The implicit modifiers.
1319     *  @throws UncheckedIOException A problem occurred when writing to the
1320     *      output target.
1321     */
1322    @SuppressWarnings( {"PublicMethodNotExposedInInterface"} )
1323    public final void emit( @SuppressWarnings( "UseOfConcreteClass" ) final CodeWriter codeWriter, final String enumName, final Set<Modifier> implicitModifiers ) throws UncheckedIOException
1324    {
1325        /*
1326         * Nested classes interrupt wrapped line indentation. Stash the current
1327         * wrapping state and put it back afterwards when this type is
1328         * complete.
1329         */
1330        final var previousStatementLine = codeWriter.statementLine();
1331        codeWriter.statementLine( -1 );
1332
1333        final var layout = codeWriter.layout();
1334
1335        try
1336        {
1337            switch( layout )
1338            {
1339                case LAYOUT_FOUNDATION -> emit4Foundation( codeWriter, enumName, implicitModifiers );
1340                case LAYOUT_DEFAULT, LAYOUT_JAVAPOET, LAYOUT_JAVAPOET_WITH_TAB -> emit4JavaPoet( codeWriter, enumName, implicitModifiers );
1341                default -> throw new UnsupportedEnumError( codeWriter.layout() );
1342            }
1343        }
1344        finally
1345        {
1346            //---* Reset the statement line *----------------------------------
1347            codeWriter.statementLine( previousStatementLine );
1348        }
1349    }   //  emit()

1352     *  Emits the type to the given code writer, using the layout as defined
1353     *  by the Foundation library code.
1354     *
1355     *  @param  codeWriter  The target code writer.
1356     *  @param  enumName    The name of the enum; can be {@code null}.
1357     *  @param  implicitModifiers   The implicit modifiers.
1358     *  @throws UncheckedIOException A problem occurred when writing to the
1359     *      output target.
1360     */
1361    protected abstract void emit4Foundation( @SuppressWarnings( "UseOfConcreteClass" ) final CodeWriter codeWriter, final String enumName, final Set<Modifier> implicitModifiers ) throws UncheckedIOException;

1363    /**
1364     *  Emits the type to the given code writer, using the layout as defined
